-- Turk Telekom Gets 239.4 Million Euros, $285.2 Million Loan
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-03-20T07:39:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/turk-telekom-gets-239-4-million-euros-285-2-million-loan-1-.html
Turk Telekomunikasyon AS (TTKOM) ,  Turkey ’s
biggest phone company, got a three-year loan of 239.4 million
euros and $285.2 million from 13 banks at an annual interest
rate of three percentage points more than the international
benchmarks.  Turk Telekom signed an accord yesterday for the “club
loan” which has a grace period of two years, it said in a
statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  today. The loan will be
used to meet working capital needs of the Ankara-based operator,
according to the statement.  Bank of America Corp. (BAC) , Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd.
and  BNP Paribas (BNP)  SA acted as lead arrangers and coordinators for
the loan, Turk Telekom said.  Export Development Canada ,  JPMorgan
Chase & Co. (JPM) , Mizuho Corporate Bank Ltd.,  Natixis (KN) , HSBC Bank Plc
and WestLB AG were also involved in the loan, it said. Other
arrangers included Standard Chartered Bank,  Citigroup Inc. (C) ,
Akbank AG and Raiffeisenlandesbank Niederoesterreich-Wien AG, it
added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
